  "body": "In Settings -> Messaging -> Contacts, ... etc I see a contact list that looks like this:\r\n\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-25 09-46-45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/170209368-3e71ab3c-0091-4d5c-ad0d-ff4811befda8.png)\r\n\r\nFirst issue here is that there's no profile picture/identity letters (this is already logged at https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/5514).\r\n\r\nHowever, what was throwing me off was that I knew I had more contacts than that, but I couldn't see them. It looks like the end of the list was reached. Turns out the other contacts are all there, just hidden in the viewport because of the available scrollable area. Inside that list, reveals the other contacts:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-25 09-46-59](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/170209872-3c04ac10-f99e-42e4-9d7b-38332fc508f9.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**We should**:\r\n\r\n1. Make sure the entire vertical space is used to display the items in that view\r\n2. If there's more items than visible, have some indication that this is a scrollable area (maybe with an inset dropshadow at the bottom of the list /cc'ing @John-44 for input)\r\n\r\nRegarding 2): the same issue arises when one has a lot of 1-on-1 chats or community channels so might be good to come up with a generic solution we can use in other places.\r\n\r\n",
